text: Fish and chips were just okay. We were on this end of the strip and decided to give it a try rather than walk down to Gordon Ramsay, but the fish and chips we had were not nearly as good here. Fish quality was probably the kicker,  as the batter and fries were pretty good.

Love the food here it's our go to every time we visit vegas and just don't want fancy but good. Always made fresh fish has light batter but huge pieces we always share a fish and shrimp basket with chowder and it's way too much food for two. It's inexpensive unlike most food in Vegas. Lots of seating around to people watch.

YES. YES and YES. The only other food to trump this joint in Vegas as far as hang over cures go is pizza. Reasonably priced. Greasy to the max. Hits the spot ever so just right. This place is also delicious when high out of your mind and aren't quite sure what the hell you're eating. Just get the family bucket meal and share with three other people. Jumbo shrimp are pretty damn jumbolicious too.

Had eaten here a few times prior... about 7 years ago and before.  Always raved about the fish 'n chips.  BEST fish ever... crispy outside, tender and flavorful inside.  So, had to stop by again to savor this treat.  Well, sadly, it's not the same as previously noted.  The first piece of fish was very good... just what I remembered... but the second piece had a distinctly "fishy" smell and flavor, like it was not fresh.  Did not finish it and very disappointed.  The chips were not crisp (McDonald's french fries are better).  So... overall, one piece was good, one was not, fries were mediocre, thus the 3 star rating.

We were really hungry and there was no line for this place so we went for it.  Turned out to be a great find.  We ordered the calamari rings and a family combo plus a few beverages.  The cost was $20--unheard of for a meal in Vegas.  We had to throw food away!  The fish planks were huge, the hush puppies were yummy, and the cole slaw fresh.  It did take a bit of time, but it was cooked to order and hot, hot, hot when we go it.  Greasy, hot food when you are hungry and tired--the best!!

Don't compare your local eatery with similar offerings on LV Blvd.  On the strip, everybody knows high prices are the norm.  Even eating at hamburger joints here can empty your wallet.  If you find cheap eats with acceptable food, you cherish that place and hold that place near to your heart.  You forgive them their flaws.

We just found Fulton Fish Market in New York, New York on the ground floor near the front entrance.  Our lunch there was decent and was easily half the price of eating at a hamburger joint.  The fish was crisp, the fries were hot.  The chowder in a bread bowl was hearty.  There were even some nice tables to sit at.  No complaints from this grateful customer.

Wanted some good clam chowder in las vegas on the strip and came across this place. I got the clam chowder and my boyfriend got the chicken and chips. The chowder was all potatoes! And runny. No clams! Had to put a ton of hot sauce to give it flavor. My boyfriend's chicken was plain and very, very oily! The best thing was had was the fries. A small soda was $3.75. Almost as much as my chowder. Do no go to this place!!!

Worst seafood ever. I feel bad for the shrimp and calamari that had to die for this, only to be prepare like hot garbage. The calamari rings are frozen from a bag and the "garlic" shrimp are actually pre cooked shrimp battered and then cooked again. Hot rubbery trash. Everything was bland. No seasoning in their batter. 

If you live near water, or eat seafood often I say never eat here. I assume the 5 star reviews are from people who don't get fresh seafood ever. 

I guess the only good thing is that it's really cheap. (You get what you pay for.) But if your in Las Vegas with hundreds of great food options, why would you ever eat frozen seafood? You could go to the grocery store anywhere in the country and buy the same product they are selling you here! Do yourself a favor and explore the Las Vegas food scene.
This is good place to get a quick snack. The service is quick and friendly. The food is very fresh.
We got the clam chowder bread bowl, calamari rings and  fries. Very good food, friendly staff(Chris and mary),very accommodating.and you can't beat those prices around here

I happened to be inside of New York New York and I happened to be hungry as well.I wasn't really in the mood to spend more than 20 bucks on a meal and wandered towards Fulton Fish Market.

As a huge fan of fish & chips ( or freedom fries as they are known in this country), I had to try out Fulton's take on the classic.

The Fish: I believe it was cod.Judging from the rubbery texture, not very fresh.As all fish does, it breaks apart very easily once you try to cut into it.I ended up just eating it with my hands.Definitely not the best tasting fish i've ever had.

The Fries: The 2nd best part of the meal.The fries were seasoned and even though you can tell they were frozen, still very good.They mix very well with the tartar sauce.

The Tartar Sauce: The best part of the meal.It hid the crappy taste of the fish and saved me from 1-starring this place.I would actually be willing to back here just to get some more of the tartar sauce.

Overall: Next time, I am splurging and going to Nine Fine Irishmen to try out their fish & chips.This is definitely not the place to go for good seafood.

Although it took forever to prepare, their fish and chips was the exact yumminess I needed to hit the spot. Their fish (cod) was fresh and nicely cooked, and the batter had a nice sweet tang to it. The greasiness is perfect for hangovers (if you happen to have one in Vegas...). There are a lot of food places in New York, New York, but this one is the best.

Came highly recommended by a friend who frequents Las Vegas several times a year and has eaten here 'more than 20 times' so maybe we hit an off day, but...

The fish was strong - not a big fan of cod as it is but mine was way to 'fishy' tasting. I prefer Halibut or Haddock but neither was on the menu.  

The batter was light and crisp which was nice - not soggy or gummy on the inside.  The fries were processed and not very good.  It honestly doesn't take much to make fries from a fresh potato so not sure why any restaurant like this would resort to frozen or whatever they were.

I wouldn't go back.  Ever.
Excellent, fresh fish.  Chowder was very tasty.  Friendly staff.  Really enjoyed eating here.  Highly recommend.

I always have a craving for Fultons when I am here at NYNY. But why? Might be the delicious flavor of the coating on the fish, shrimp and chicken. The hush puppies are great too. But  just remember, when you eat here it's very greasy.....but delicious!

I am still craving your fish and chips so bad. It was so delicious.
I really love the set up for these restaurants at NY NY casino. Very cute and cozy.
But this spot is a must try. Yummy!!
Fish and chips were pretty good. Hush puppies and coleslaw were good. I enjoyed the experience.

My boyfriend and I got the fish and chips and the chicken and chips and it was AMAZING!!! Seriously the best fried fish I have ever had. Not too oily which I don't like too oily, and the best fries ever. Crispy on the outside and soft on the inside and perfectly seasoned. 100% would recommend. And cheap! It was like 8.50 a plate.

Located inside NY NY off the casino floor. You order your food at the counter and wait while it is cooked to order for you.  The most amazing fish and chips I have eaten as well as their clam strips, which I cannot say enough good about.  The fish is fried to perfection as well as their French fries.  Crunchy on the outside and flaky and tender on the inside.  Clams were not the least bit chewy.  Did I mention the prices and portion sizes were amazing!
Kudos to the owner and staff for running an immaculate place that serves amazing food.  I look forward to my visits to Vegas so that I can eat here again and again!

Was looking for something simple and quick to grab and sit down to enjoy. Located inside New York New York hotel next a good selection of other places to eat. Food wasn't greasy and very reasonably priced.

I was staying at Luxor and wanted something cheap and quick. I wasn't feeling any of the options at my hotel or Luxor, so I trekked a little farther over to NYNY. I found Fulton Fish Frye and I love seafood, so I decided to give it a try. I got the fish, shrimp, and chicken meal. It comes with two jumbo butterfly shrimp, two chicken strips, and two pieces of fish. All of these items are seriously HUGE and they tasted great. The meal also comes with seasoned fries, coleslaw, and two hush puppies. I didn't taste the coleslaw (never tasted one I liked, so I stopped trying), so I can't say anything besides they give you a huge portion of it. The fries were a little bland for being "seasoned", and the hush puppies were great but they were super tiny. All that food was only $12.95! Even though it doesn't come with a drink, I thought it was a great deal and I'd definitely make the walk for it again.

Fulton fish frye
Some people will eat anything.Their taste buds don't work.
Maybe the owner fired the yacking   hispanic non working two women on shift.If so good for you!!!

This is my hubby's favorite clam chowdah spot and he was so excited to take me when we planned our trip to Vegas. 

Now that I've tried this clam chowder that he talks about from time to time, I think it's pretty good. But not the best clam chowder I've had. It doesn't compare to the ones I've had in the Bay Area. With that said, they do give a huge portion for $6 + tax. There is a good amount of clams and it also comes with ham that gives off a subtle smokey flavor. It's creamy and the bread bowl is fluffy and soft. 

This clam chowder definitely makes the list of good cheap eats for sure. I can see college kids making their Vegas trip worthwhile at a joint like this. I guess now that I've past my college years, I'm a bit "bougie" with my food perhaps. But good chowder. Kudos to my hubby.
Excellent fish and hush puppies. Not overly heavy, good quality fish. Substantial serving. Very polite gentlemen behind the counter- two of them. Smiles and politeness. Very nice.

Pleasantly surprised. Clams were outstanding. Huge & tender rather than tough & chewy. Some of the best I've ever had the pleasure of devouring. They were made to order & perfectly cooked. Hubby had the fish & chicken. He loved it. Great tarter. The bread bowl itself was good, but we've had better clam chowder. It was decent but we weren't "wowed". The seafood however wowed us, especially for for the price!

Really sorry soggy tasting no season imitation tasting fish and shrimp. I wouldn't feed this to my dog. It was very very very poorly prepared and No seasoning! Even after I added salt and pepper the taste did not improve!!!very bland taste. Do Not waste your time or money!
Didn't look fancy. Thought twice about it. But it was delicious. Creamy traditional clam chowder in bread bowl and perfectly hot and fried fish and chips. Excellent for the price.

It was alright.  While staying t New York New York we have walked by this place many times but never stopped in part because there was never a line and also because sometimes it smelled too fishy.  We finally decided to give it a try.  The fish was crisp and not anymore greasy than anywhere else.  The service was a little show.  I cannot say I would go back but I cant say for sure I would not if I got desperate for a fried fish fix.  However I am not a huge fish eater and if it even begins to smell fishy its not for me.   I will say what we had did not taste that way.

A nice stand located on the first floor of New York, New York. We got the family meal which had fried fish, fried chicken, popcorn shrimp, seasoned fries, hush puppies and coleslaw. We also got their clam chowder bowl. As a family of 5, everyone was able to get a ton of food! Super delicious and enough leftovers to probably feed 3 more people. Definitely recommend going for a quick lunch!

Pros: located in NYNY. Huge portions 
Cons: Snappy cashier, fish tasted weird

My family and I wanted to go to New York, New York to get something to eat. My father, an avid seafood eater, was drawn to the Fulton Fish Market. 

We ordered the family meal (around $20) which included chicken, fish, hush puppies, french fries, coleslaw and shrimp. My dad asked for more chicken and less fish because I can't eat too much fish and my mom detests fish. The cashier simply rolled her eyes and was very rude. Umm...sorry? Not cool. 

Everything was great except the soggy and bland fish, which wasn't seasoned well at all. We ended up wasting most of it. 

I'm not too sure I would go here again...I'll probably pass it up in favor of that upbeat looking Mexican restaurant next door.

Some people talk about Earl's Sandwiches  the same way my boyfriend and I talk about Fulton's fish and chips! 

The menu is simple yet it reminds me a lot of KFC with their family portion options, sides, etc. The line was long, the wait was moderate,  but the smell alone made me want to stay in line. I ordered the fish and chips and some calamari. It was ready in about ten minutes. The size of the fish was just right and looked so crispy yet flaky already! The taste? Straight up mouth watering. The calamari, yeah that was bomb too. 

It's a must to come back and try some more out on the menu because there is a variety of appetizing choices.

This place was pretty good. There sauces were great, prices were ok (i guess damn great for Vegas is more like it), and the fish was awesome.  I got the fish and chips which comes with 2 huge filets atop a basket of fries/"chips".  The fries are just ok. Nothing a little ketchup couldn't help, but the fish... Oh my goodness. I shared the basket with my sis, and after a fish and some fries each, we were stuffed. Definitely a good/cheap/different eat in Vegas. And def waaaaaaayyyyy cheaper than the other fish and chips/pub type place in the same hotel. I don't know what it was called, some sit down.  This one was basically a food court kinda deal.  Its downstairs and towards the back btw.  Def go back.
This is just not good. Poor. Barely a handful of fries and some fat chicken 'tenders'. Overpriced, not worth it and well, just not any good.

The fish and chips are amazing! We also ordered the clams, they were only ok. The fish is hand dipped and delicious! Totally worth the price! The pieces of fish were big and easily could be shared between 2 adults.

I've always gotten good food when I come here. In this instance, we arrived about 12:45pm on a Sunday before a Knights game. It took 20 minutes from the time we got in line to when we got our food. 

The clam chowder is so good!  I find it pretty filling by itself so skipped the bread bowl. 2 of us also shared an order of fish and chips.  I thought that was plenty of food.

Had the fish and chips which is reasonably priced meal for Las Vegas. 2 good size pieces of fried fish that was crispy on the outside and mild flavored filet on the inside. Grab a  table across from their counter and eat.

If you like fish and chips you should like this place.  Prices are very reasonable and portions are good size. The cole slaw could use some work but the fish and chicken make up for it.  So next time you are hungry and are near or in NYNY and are looking for something good and quick this is the place.

Staff here was pretty good but definitely the only bad meal i have ever had in vegas in all the years i have been here.  Ordered the fish, shrimp, and chicken dinner and it was extremely greasy and had no taste. I know there were a few people ahead of me and maybe the oil wasnt up to temp when it was cooked because it was just saturated in grease.  My wife and i ended up throwing it away and spent the rest of the night rolling around feeling groggy from the portion we did eat.  Guess thats what i get for ordering fish in the desert lol.  There reviews on here seem pretty decent so maybe we just picked a bad time.

After going to a Halloween party and drinking, it sounded like a good idea to eat something that would absorb the alcohol.  We ordered Fish and Chips.  

The chips were good but the fish was not fresh and smelled so bad that I couldn't even finish my first bite.  I am sure the person cooking it knew the fish was not good but still decided to serve it.  Yes! smelled that bad

This had to be the worst meal I've had in Vegas.  Will not be coming back here again.
Simple menu, gets the job done for fish-n-chips at a inexpensive price for Las Vegas.
Always a must visit spot for us when visiting Las Vegas!! For $20.00, you receive a ton of food, easily can feed 3-4 people with chicken, fish, hushpuppies, fries, coleslaw and breaded shrimp.

Place was good. Got the fish, shrimp and chicken special with chips for about $12. The breading was a bit too much and the chips weren't that great but still good for the amount of food and the price.

Stopped for a quick snack, fries were hot and spiced perfectly. Calamari looks like onion rings but is really good, not chewy -  just right amount of batter... Dipping sauce was uniquely tasty.  Hit the spot!

Batter coated thick cod, fried with the perfect crunch neither undercooked or over cooked earns my 4 stars.  
I also had their calamari rings which was again the perfect crunch and cook time.  However, having already a favorite place for fish and chips, I couldn't give them one more star because their seafood sauce and tarter sauce could use some working on.  I also had their clam  chowder bowls and again, if you are at awe for  "Splash Cafe" clam chowder, then theirs was "just".
I would most recommend their fried items.  They are definitely experts at doing that.  
And!!! Thank you to the young gentlemen who was always pleasant and so courteous with giving me my cup of water.  Thank you for taking your time to give me ice.  On another order, another young gentleman when I asked for a cup of water, didn't even take his time to put ice. This guy was actually looking like a grumpy gumby.

Points: Awesome clam chowder. Large pieces of fish. Good flaky fish. The chicken and shrimp are bland, shrimp not too fresh.

Our group was in a hurry to make it to the last showing of Zumanity so we decided to find somewhere to eat in New York New York. I'm not a fan of a sit down restaurant when I go to Vegas. I'm all about the buffets and trying out little shops like this place. Plus, a nice sit down place would require a lot of waiting around for servers, looking over a big menu, etc. This place had a line of 5 or so, after ordering, it took another 5 to get my food.

I've never been here before and since I was the only one who decided not to spend almost $100 a person (my group went to Gallagher's steakhouse) I ordered the combo that had chicken, fish, shrimp, hush puppies & fries so I can try everything. This is why eating with a group is better. everyone can order one thing and try everything. I love clam chowder and decided to get a cup/bowl of that too (don't like bread so no bread bowl for me)

THE CLAM CHOWDER IS AMAZING! I don't know if they laced it with crack but it was the most amazing chowda I've ever had. I've had some good ones in Boston, but this was awesome, fresh chunky clams, possibly a hint of bacon? I could do without the potatoes in it though. If you past by and there's no line, get a cup!

The fish was nicely fried, not too thick of a batter, the meat was flaky and tasted fresh. the chicken strip was pretty nasty and had no flavor, I would have been moist cardboard that's been fried... just don't get the chicken. Shrimp was okay, but I can tell by the texture that they were not fresh.....I'm not saying I expect live shrimp to be flown into Las Vegas! But it's probably been sitting UNFROZEN for too long.

New York New York did it right, there are plenty of seats and tables along the "streets" so get a tray of food and enjoy!

Stayed at NY NY and thought the Family Meal provided here would be a good option for us (2 adults and 2 kids). Boy, was I wrong! We ate around 6 pm. 

First, I was told they were out of hush puppies as part of the family meal, but they would add a piece of chicken instead. Then, we were told they were ALSO out of the shrimp (as part of the family meal), so I asked if they could sub fried clams instead of fried shrimp and was immediately told "no, but we can give you another piece of chicken". I immediately questioned this since a piece of chicken is not comparable to fried shrimp and they asked if I wanted to talk to the manager. I replied "yes", not realizing this meant I would need to call the manager on the phone. 

**Side Rant: if you are going to be out of two items included in a Family Meal deal, either make a decision beforehand, or empower your employees to make a decision on substitutions that make sense. Rant over. 

The manager ended up substituting the clam strips for the shrimp. 

My son ordered the clam chowder served in a sourdough bread bowl and they served it in a plastic bowl with a slice of bread in a plastic container for him. What a joke!

Overall, the food was okay. The clam strips and the fish were good. Nobody wanted to eat the chicken and the waffle fries were way overcooked. 

Would not recommend.

I love this place!!!!
Everytime I am in Vegas, I make sure I go to the NY NY casino for lunch. 
Their fish n chips is so delicious. The fish is always cooked perfect.... crunchy from outside, flakey inside.
The shrimp is really good n tasty too.
Their clam chowder is the best chowder I ever had...
All their food is delicious and worth every penny.

First I have to say that their food is great, every time I come to Vegas, I want their fish.  The review is about their service and hours.  They are listed to be open from 11am till 11pm everyday.  The last two trips I have taken to Vegas I have gone to get fish around 10 to take to the room, to find them already closing!  Ask the guys working what time they close, they say 11, it is only 10, we closed early. The last trip I decided I would question management, this girl that came out had no idea what customer service is.  No apology for the inconvenience, basically said I don't care.  My question is, the order we were going to place would have around $100, and if we wanted fish, who is to say that others might as well.  She said they close early when it is slow, why we stood their questioning them closing early, 3 others walked up to find them closed!  I question is that being slow or are they just lazy and want to go home.  Not sure most malls like this have contractual agreements on hours!  Maybe a few fines for closing early and they will stop!  If you want good service, just go next door to Gonzalez y Gonzalez!

Just okay. I got two huge pieces of fish in my meal, and while the size was impressive, I can still taste the first piece I ate 5 hours after I've finished my meal. WAY too fishy. The second piece was better but my impression was tainted by the fishy first piece. I didn't get the shrimp but my table mates did and they looked delicious. Fries were also just ok. Tartar sauce was really good, but didn't redeem everything else. Next time I'm at NY NY and need to eat, I'll get a sandwich from the deli.

Terrible, can-based clam chowder served cold and they refused to reheat it or give me a new fresh batch. It was served so cold that one could feel that thick layer of fat on my palate and tongue. The worst part is they were already making a new batch and they didn't offer to give me a new one. But the thing is there's no excuse we're waiting 20 minutes just to get served cold chowder. There should always be a hot batch ready to go. In the end, I got my money back.

Tasty deep fried battered fish and chicken strips.  Consistent quality (for my two widely spaced visits)  Curiously the family meal deal is the most economical for two - come hungry.  Id pass on the hush puppies.  If you can bring your own drink or bottle of water.

For about $10, you get 2 pieces of good sized fish and a generous amount of seasoned fries. The fish wasn't overly breaded nor greasy. Fries were pretty good too, the pepper seasoning is a nice touch. 

They also honored my request for an extra container of tartar sauce at no charge. We shared an order of hush puppies, which were also good. 

Considering the location at the NYNY, you'll be hard pressed to beat the value.

I like it. I've visited NYNY a lot of times, and have tried almost all the restaurants in that square. i must say this is my favorite- of all the fast food shops. 

The batter is nice. Greasy, yes. But it's fish and chips people. The fries or "chips" could be better. The calimari is ok; chicken strips are rather weird with the same beer batter meant for the fish. The actual battered fish is firm in texture, and holds up to the batter and oil, etc. I like their hush puppies as well.

Will return when on my next visit.
Not crazy about deep fried food BUT this place has by far the BEST batter I've had on fried foods. LOVE the fish n chips and fried chicken strips. We always come back for more!

We likey! Similar to long john silvers with a lil boost. If you like fried seafood and dont have much cash, Come here. Get the clam chowder bread bowl! I also tried fried butterfly shrimp with fries. No complaints. Coleslaw could have been sweeter, but im an east coast girl. Maybe ours is different.

For some food court cookin', this place has got some REALLY tasty fish and chips! The cod is fried up nicely. Comes out with the perfect textures and.... It's VERY affordable!

The batter is not too thick, not too thin, crispy  and just right. They got pretty solid chicken and shrimp too... 

I would come to the New York New York hotel again just to get me some of this!

This was a late night dinner. We did not want anything too crazy so we tried fish and chips at Fulton. The fish was fried to order along with the fries. 

We also got chowder.

It was not the best chowder and the fish was so-so. It's was still very crispy but I wanted more than two pieces for the price.

I would recommend to get the ny style pizza instead. If you plan to eat 2 slices and you have more than two- grab the large!

Delicious fish n chips omg I had the cod fillets and the chips were fresh N better then any fries I've ever had... the tarter sauce could use some work  but the service was sweet and fast I had spent about 8 bucks and its well worth it too...so if ur in town at new york new york in vegas annnnd you love fish n chips..you will enjoy this place. I also got to try the fried clamari, and clam chowder served in a freshly baked bread bowl. This food was super fresh and tasted authentic as if these were the first fish n chips created and i was the first person to discover them...OOO yess they were that Good. O heads up for all you salty people...meaning the batter doesnt have any special seasoning you pretty much taste fresh fish with a delicioud batter, so i could see why some people may think it can come off bland but whtever everyone is entitled to thier opinion...

Was in Las Vegas on business and wanted fish & chips and this place came up with reasonable reviews.  Should have known better when I saw it was in a food court in the casino.  
Food was hot, plentiful and okay tasting but that's about all you can say for this place....

I grew  up in MA eating too much clam chowder. The clam chowder back there is always fresh, never too heavy, perfect amount of potato to soup ratio and a large handful of clam. Fulton's is the closest to that clam chowder that I have tasted out west, and I will happily eat there several times a month if possible.

Is Fulton's chowder pretty creamy? Sure. Is MA chowdah (I had to)super creamy? It's not supposed to be, but that's okay and forgivable. There are worse seafood sins to commit. I love that it tastes fresh and that oh, it's gluten free! Nothing else at this restaurant is gluten free, but this chowder is and I LOVE IT! Many chowders thicken with a rue. Not Fulton's. Straight cream and the natural starchiness of the potatoes make this soup divine. I love that it isn't too salty, piping hot, and for those who can, grab that sourdough bread bowl to put it in (even though I think that's a crime, but moving forward).

My mother in law, husband's, uncle, aunt and cousin (all from Scotland)feel that Fulton's has some of the best fish and chips in the U.S. When compared to the homeland of fish and chips, it is still very good, and that is saying a lot. Consistent in quality, not overly greasy, HUGE portion (easily able to split it between two people), and flaky, delicious and even the chips are great. Drizzle some malt vinegar on those bad boys and my husband and his family are very, very happy and continue to go there each time they visit. Great value for the money you spend, and a nice quick bite that isn't so hard on your budget. Like I said, my entire family could eat there every day if we let them. Delicious!

Looove this place! Who would have thought getting excellent fish and chips in the New York New York Hotel in Las Vegas?? This is my 3rd trip here and this is still the best!!

The fish cod is nicely fried with just enough batter to make them crispy and a gold brown. Not over-fried and dried out like most places I've been that even specialize in fish chips. The fries are crisp and not limp. Perfect!! The whole thing doesn't look like much and you may be tempted to get a side dish, but eat the fish and chips first because the fillet can be filling along with the fries. Great for sharing and even though it make a little time especially when they're busy, it is well worth the wait. 

This place is located downstairs from the arcade and in the food court section. There's plenty of seating all around the recreation of Greenwich Village. They have other items on their menu and I think I recall the clam chowder is pretty good. When I get over how good the fish and chips are, I'll try something else from them. I can taste them already....
AWESOME Fish and chips! I am a big fan of fish and chips, so we had to try it. This place did not disappoint at all. I would definitely come back.
The Triple F is an excellent place to grab a quick bite while in NYNY. Can't go wrong with their Fish & Chips!

Excellent fry batter, had the fish and chicken.

Chicken tenders were good, but the fish stole the show. 

This place is a great deal on the Strip and very reasonably priced. I believe the fish and chicken was $8.50 for two pieces of fish and two pieces of tenders. The dish came with fries.

Tartar sauce and malt vinegar accompany the fish. 

I didn't expect to enjoy this place so much, but it really pleasantly surprised me. I'm really glad I tried this place.

The batter is better than many other batters. This place is really worth a visit, tourist or not!

good stuff! we tried a variety of items and it was all good. I recommend the calamari as it is all rings and has a great batter. the fries are excellent as well. I took off one star as it is a little tough to find seating. otherwise, prices are fair and the food is good.

Want to make a cow happy? Then eat fish! 

Prefer your fish not taste like fish? Then their fish and chips will fit the bill.

Located on the casino floor of New York New York, it's in the area where it looks like you're on the sidewalks of a city.  Hey, it's New York City!

The fried fish and fries were tasty.  Not healthy mind you, but tasty just the same.  And the fish gives you a second level utility in that you can imagine the fried batter soaking up the Vegas spirits and cheer you have sloshing around in your belly. 

Fried up when you order so it can take a few minutes before you dig in.  Place your order and scope out a table near by.  You'll pick up your meal at the counter.  This is inside sidewalk style dining (not restaurant in case you were wondering).

We were eager to make a return visit to this fish & chips place because my wife enjoy it so much the last time we came to Las Vegas and ate here 3 times.  Unlike that visit though, this time the wait wasn't nearly as long for the food and....perhaps it should have been as the fish were undercooked and something on the slimy side.   Now the fries were quite tasty and crisp, but that wasn't nearly enough to offset the disappointment of crappy cooking, even if the pieces were once again gigantic.      Whether this was a one time screw up on their part or not, it's not likely we'd think about coming here again, as much as we love fish n' chips.

The fried clams and fried calamari here is pretty good.  The seafood tastes fresh and the breading is tasty.  The service, however, can be pretty bad - maybe I just came here late or something, but the guys who worked here weren't very friendly and seemed a little irritable.

This place reminded me of food from a sporting event.  It looked very similar to a chicken tender platter you wound get at a baseball game, and it costs the same as well.  I would much prefer to go to a pub, sit down, and pay a little more than eat here again.  The fish and chips were only slightly worse than the average pub, but they were way too expensive and nowhere near the quality that the price deemed, while the portions were not big enough as well.  There are plenty of other restaurant to try out rather than Fulton Fish Frye in New York New York alone.  Even try Nine Fine Irishman around the corner for a cool atmosphere and sharable fish and chips that are more authentic and probably double the portion.

Surprisingly the second best fish fry I've ever had AND it's less than $10 (the best fish fry I had was when I went walleye fishing in Minnesota, so nothing beats freshly caught fish).  

Located in NYNY Hotel and Casino, it's surrounded by a bunch of other restaurants.  You place your order at the window and find seating near by.  I went for lunch and at the time, there were plenty of people walking around, but there was plenty of seating around the area.  

I got the fish and chips for about $8.  Came with 2 large battered filet of cod and large wedge fries.  Also tried the calamari.  

The fish was lightly battered and the flavor was perfect.  Lightly crispy on the outside, soft and tender on the inside.  The fish filets were so large that I could only eat one (one and a half at the most).  You can dip it in tartar sauce, but it was also good without.  The fries were more like wedges, and they were perfectly seasoned.  

This is a great place for lunch if you're looking to spend less than $10.

I was pleasantly surprised with Fulton Fish Market. My wife and I were starving and ordered their family meal deal. We were warned it would be too much food for us but we insisted because of how hungry we were. They were right, it was too much!

The food was all excellent, the fish was crispy and not too greasy and their chicken planks were very tender and juicy. Considering we were in a popular casino, the value was off the charts.
Good tasty food but SUPER, SUPER oily. Only good for hangover cures. Other than that, it's too oily to stomach.

Kind of a bummer when the first thing you see after placing your order is the lady reaching for a huge pre-sealed bag of mass-produced hush puppies in the freezer. I could get that at Costco. Needless to say, those weren't great. The fish and chips did seem to be breaded and battered fresh from a station in the kitchen. The two pieces of fish are served on a huge bed of seasoned fries. The seasoning didn't really work for me... I would have preferred just a straight-up type of steak fry. I experienced major inconsistencies between the two pieces of fish. One was very thin with more breading and batter than actual fish. The other was a thicker piece of fish and absolutely delicious. Overall, a solid value for the strip in Vegas.

I usually love this place, but not today, I got there about 10-15 before close and the dude said we're closed, however it's not 11p yet, he looked at me crazy and shrugs his shoulders and said too bad...come on NyNy, you have to do better

So, after wandering The Strip forever in a daze trying to decide on what to eat, I suddenly had the urge for Fish and Chips and a Clam Chowder Bread Bowl. I didn't really want to go to a sit down place and have to pay a tip or be in a loud atmosphere, so I wondered if there possibly was a place where I could find such a thing. I wandered in and out of each hotels' food court areas and kept coming up empty. Just when I was about to throw in the towel, I wandered into NY NY and almost broke down out of hunger and went for something else when this place came into sight. I could hear angels singing as I approached it. They had Fish and Chips AND Clam Chowder in a Bread Bowl. SCORE!!!! There were a lot of people in line and there was only two guys working. They were busting their butts to fulfill orders. I ordered what I wanted and made it a Meal Deal which added on a Soda and Cole Slaw for another $2.50. My bill came to around $15. 

I waited in anticipation of that CC Bread Bowl. I waited. And waited. And waited. Then when my order was 'ready,' I was informed that they ran out of Chowder! The fat cow that was ahead me got the last of it! Dammit!! She took away the one simple joy in my life whenever I go visit somewhere. Aaaarrrrrgggghhh!! The guy said I could have whatever else was on the menu to replace it. I chose the closest thing and got some clam strips. Just not the same, but it will have to do. 

I was served my new order and grabbed a seat. The Fish and Chips came with three large pieces of fried cod and some tasty length wise cut wavy fries. I really enjoyed the fish. I found it to be meaty and I know it was freshly cooked because you can watch them cook it. The fried clam strips were okay. I haven't had them in a long time. The strips weren't very big. Damn, I wanted that CCBB. By the time I ate all the fried goodness, I didn't have enough room for the Cole Slaw. It was pretty big and I just saved it for later. 

I hope that lady enjoyed my Chowder. I know I would have.

Greasy Seafood Joint. I like it. I had a hankering for Calamari prior to watching Zumanity... cost me $8+ Beats the hell out of going to one of the seafood restaurants or casino cafe for twice the price.

The lady (in line) in front of me ordered the Family Meal.. hot damn! That's a bucket of Fish and Chips and I'm not sure what else.. but it feeds your clan without breaking your bank!
Pretty mediocre.  Chicken tasted rubbery, cocktail sauce was really gross.  The people were nice, though.  I had no problem getting free tap water with my meal.

We stopped into the New York Casino and saw the Fulton Fish place. We checked the food and prices and they seemed great the food is fresh and made fresh. The chef is very good and they are a small place so you might have to wait a few after you order. Because they make it fresh as you order. And it's worth the wait.
Very fresh fish & chips!  The order came with two big piece of fish, and lots of fries.

The Fish Market is one of those little shops found in the Village Eateries of the NY NY hotel,  located "down the street" from Gonzales Y Gonzales.  
Including  the fish market in the eateries re-creates that "Manhattan feel" within the village section of the casino.
The food found in the market is the standard fare of Fish and Chips, Chicken strips and Fries or Shrimp and fries. They serve hush puppies and cole slaw as extras with the meal. 
A stop at the fish market provides you an excellent quick lunch which far exceeds the standard food court experience of other casinos. Once you have your lunch tray and basket of fish, a close by table calls out to you to sit, eat and people watch while you enjoy your meal. 
For you bargain hunters - Fish and Chips in the Nine Fine Irishmen is @ 17.99, at Fulton's Market it is 6.99. You choose the ambiance you want.

We rarely find a fish fry we like. We have one we compare others to and rarely find one we will go back and eat at if in the area. This one is a keeper! Oh my goodness! The cod fillets are huge! I could barely eat one. The batter is just perfect, crispy and not greasy. I didn't even touch the "chips" because I was so full from the fish. My husband got the shrimp and chicken and fell in love with the place. He isn't a big fan of fried fish but loved the cod here. We will definitely go back, The prices are very reasonable. I think it was the cheapest dinner we had in our three days there. It was $8.95 for a two piece fish and chips. So worth it! Can't say enough good things about the food here. The fish tasted fresh, too, not frozen fresh. It is in the quick bites area of NY NY, so it isn't fancy. Plenty of tables, though, in the courtyard. When we asked for extra tartar sauce, they were not stingy. We had more than enough.

Ok at best. The chowder sucks, it barely has anything in it. A few potatoes, haven't tasted a piece of clam yet. 
My JD has some overpriced plate that let me bump it up 1 star to two. People at the next table left most of it here. I guess they weren't satisfied either. Look elsewhere.

Cheap prices for Vegas standards, but you get what you paid for. I'm not expecting ocean fresh seafood, but you could at least know the ingredients in your frozen quick-fry varieties instead of looking at each other like "uhhhh I don't know?"

I'll admit that when it was piping hot, it was pretty good though. I would peg this as good for a late night snack after Zumanity or for NY-NY guests that don't feel like wandering back out to the strip, but nothing more.
Not bad for fast food. The fish was good the chicken was just ok the shrimp  was not what we was looking for if I visit Ny Ny again I will pass up on this spot and try one of the other places

We are craving calamari suddenly so we searched around and found this place. I actually preferred the tentacles more than the rings. Usually the rings have a slightly frozen flavour , but luckily the batter this time was pretty good! It's still a little greasy:)... but the service was fast!

Still looking for tentacles though...

We only had their clam chowder in a sourdough bread bowl and it was amazing! My husband said it was the best clam chowder he's had since he left Connecticut. We will definitely be back! The price is great and the customer service was awesome!

Wasn't one of the places I have bookmarked to eat at in Vegas but I cant get my way for eating everytime with 10+ people.
I got the fish and chips and my daughter got the clam chowder bowl.
Wasn't expecting much but both are very good. If I had to eat here again I would for sure.

Just your average fish & chips. The fish was great along with the fries. The tartar sauce was okay. I would still come here again if we were craving fish & chips. You can get as many vinegar packets as you want.

So the wife and I had a loooooong night and needed some nice greasy food to fix is up. What better than some good ol' Fish N Chips for breakfast! Mind you, we both love, crave and breath seafood. We had eaten here before in the past (2008) and really enjoyed it, however this past experience 9/12 was extremely disappointing. 

The food court had just opened up and we were the only ones in line and ready to chow down. The food took almost 10 minutes to make but considering it had just opened I didn't frown too much on it. However the smell fishy scent made us want to gag. The first piece of fish was delicious. Moist, tender on the side and crispy on the outside. 

The second piece of fish smelled like the San Francisco wharf! I had notice my wife stopped eating and poured more vinegar on her fish, as soon as I bite into my fish I realized why. I don't know what happened, rather the deep fryers not hot enough, fish poor quality or simply not cooked long enough. Irregardless we were not finishing this plate. 

Unfortunately, we discarded the stinky plates and fulfilled our appetite with a piece of pizza next door. Most likely next time we're in the City of Sin, we will not me back.

Place is a small window to order from in side New York casino. Food court area. I'm not from the east coast or anything. And as far as I've heard they are known for their fried clams and what not. Never had them but I've heard good things about them. Their clam chowder and fish and chips are the bomb though! Both of which I had  Obvi. But really good food and usually under 10$ for clam chowder with a sourdough bread bowl! I won't compare their bread bowl to paneer bread bakery but still good bread and really really good soup. Fish and chips are gold and crisp. French fries made pretty good too. Like actual  fries. Not processed potato. Been here a few times and will come back. I recommend this joint!!

Not the friendliest or accommodating staff, but this was the one place I felt like we didn't get gouged and actually got decent portions/quality for what we paid. The fish was a tad fishy smelling, though, but we were starving and it still tasted good so we finished it anyway. Fish was a little overcooked, but still good. This isn't a must -go or anything, but it'll do in a pinch and was satisfying. I would only give this place 3 stars at home, but in light of everything else in Vegas, it gets am extra star for value!

Is it just me or is it hard to find a quick and relatively cheap place to eat in veags? There are just too much sit down/nice and $$ places.

NY NY really wins at providing quick and good stuff.... they have multiple resturants that are quick and not too bad money wise. I would have to say fulton's is one of the best.

The fish was good (ive had better), but the chicken was AMAZING. Some of the best fried chicken I have had. Hot and juicy!! Full of flavor!!  It is situated in the part of NY NY that is styled like city streets so there is ample open sidewalk-style seating. Very nice.

Aaah fish and chips!! They're really good here and made fresh.  The pieces of fish are decent sized.  (you get 2 in your order.)  This time I also tried the chicken & chips. Those weren't bad either and surprisingly the meat was tender. 
Their chips (or fries) are seasoned and they have good flavor to them.
Also, don't be scared to ask for extra sauce (like tartar and ketchup). They don't charge extra and willingly give you more.

New England clam chowder in sourdough bowl. Very good. Fish,shrimp,chicken,hush puppy's and fries. One of the best fish n chips around!
Chicken was very good too! Glad we ate here!
Awesome New England clam chowder bread bowls! Would definitely recommend stopping by this place inside the New York New York! It didn't disappoint

The food is pretty good. I love the fish, the fish is deep fried but light and crispy..not to heavy. I also had "jumbo shrimp" which was tasty but very small.
THE CLAM CHOWDER IS THE BESTEST
The workers seem to be very introverted,
They don't smile much. I think that the workers hate their jobs. The food 5stars -  The service 0stars

Typically I try a place twice before doing an actual review but this fish fry place is quick, fresh, & very reasonable pricing. 
The fish, chicken, shrimp, frys, & hush-puppies was like $12..could have paid $30 elsewhere for something like this...
Yum.
Boyfriend & I were impressed!
Was looking for good place to eat. Saw this on here and decided to try it. Had the family deal,which can easily feed 3 to 4! Food was fresh,hot and large portions.

Fulton's has always been a must- have favorite over the years, but not after yesterday. It's been a couple years since I've been in town long enough to grab my favorite fish n chips, and was disappointed to see that they changed the batter. It used to be golden brown, light, fluffy, and crispy but my meal yesterday evening was far from what I remember Fulton's to be. Bring the old batter back please!

$5.95 for a bowl of clam chowder and a bread bowl in NYNY?!  It seemed too good to be true and it was.  :(  They ran out of bowls and offered no discount or subs on the missing loaf.  The chowder itself was tasty but lukewarm at most.  Def no need to try this again.  Bummer...

Super tasty fish - cole slaw was dry as it should be and fabulous for those who like it that way!  Fries were ok - I like seasoned and thick cut like they were, they just were not as fresh as everything else. Great service too - if you are looking for a relatively inexpensive and tasty dinner of fish and chips - great place to go!!!

My husband and I ordered the fish & shrimp with chips. About $23 for both of us. The fries were seasoned and delicious. The same goes for the shrimp and fish, tarter sauce and cocktail sauce was good too! It was a good cheap eat as we were waiting to see zumanity show.

Just checked it and got the luggage upstairs, time for a snack. Walking through New York New York is this sweet spot of what seems to be an endless street of eateries. 
All fried to order were my huge peices of cod and my tasty hush puppies. Even the frys were hot. All at a fair price.
Not a destination food palace more like a oasis in the desert. Sweet.

These Fish and Chips are actually pretty GOOD!! Really people, for less than $12 bucks in Vegas, a decent and filling meal. I got the 2 piece Cod with Chips and drown it down with my Diet soda (it help cut the grease!). Tossed some malted vinegar and tar tar sauce and wholla...Happy Meal in Vegas...but seriously this is pretty Good kidding aside!!! Nice part of the NY Casino in a mock street atmosphere.

I always order from here Fish & Chips and Clam Chowder in a sourdough bread, and the foods almost never disappoint.  I'd rate it somewhere in between 3 and 4 stars as i'm not really a fan of Fulton but the food is definitely more than A-OK.  It's sorta pricey though; for one order of Fish & Chips, one clam chowder, and one large diet Pepsi, total is 18 something dollars.  If you wanna refill your soda, pay an extra $1.66.  I think i still like Fulton, but have found something better (lobster chowder!!) from the food court at Ceasar's Palace.

Worth the wait, open late. The food served hot and fresh with great portions sizes. I felt the fish had a great crisp to it and it wasn't overcooked which is pretty common with fried fish. They serve vinegar with your chips and pepper and that was all it needed. Good sized shrimp come with the last combo are very plump and crispy.

Love the fish and chicken. Unlike allot of places out west fulton has hush puppies. I'm from Tennessee so I love hush puppies. 
Staff is very friendly. Very clean restaurant. Great seating. 
Ive been deveral times now. My ONLY problem with this restaurant is they are slow! If you have time to wait I highly recommend this place but if not don't stop. For me the wait is worth it.
I will definitely go back.

Fried goodness. This place definitely reminded me of the county fair since I looked at my tray filled with fried chicken strips, fried fish, and fries. On a healthier, less-fried note, I also got the bread bowl filled with clam chowder. 

The food was good but wasn't anything special. The fish and chips were pretty greasy and the pieces of fish were large and juicy...but it was expected. The chicken strips were also not bad. The soup was pretty tasty but did not have enough clams. Sad. 

This is a good place to stop by to get a quick, cheap bite in the NYNY food court. Just be aware of getting greasy fingers.

While walking through New York New York, I was excited to see this place. I love seafood and knew I had to try it out. They sell fried fish fillets, fried chicken planks, fried shrimp, fried calamari rings, fried clams, and clam chowder.

First off, their fried items are fresh. It doesn't come frozen when they fry it. You can actually see them dipping the items in batter and frying it. After seeing all of this, I couldn't wait. However, it was a bit of a let down.

We ordered the fish and chips, fried clams, and clam chowder in a bread bowl. All of this came out close to $30, with the addition of the add on meal. For $4 more, you get a large drink with a cole slaw.

I really wanted to try the clam chowder. That's my soup of choice. I just wanted it in a cup. They only offer it in the bread bowl so I was forced to get it. The soup was good. It had chunks of clam and potato in it. It wasn't overly salty. I ended up throwing the bread bowl away.

The menu was misleading. I ordered fried clams, I got fried clam STRIPS. Most of the clam strips were tiny and it was all breading. The fries that it came with were huge and crispy.

My husband's meal came with two big pieces of fried fish. I tried a bite of it and it was the best thing that was ordered. The fish was moist and smooth on the inside of the hot, crispy breading.
Great place for a quick meal. The fish and chips are excellent and served in an ample portion. Prices are very reasonable.

Eating cheap on vacation is always priority number uno. I've sort of turned it into a game: find the tastiest meals for as little money as possible. I think I really nailed the game this trip as I discovered a few golden joints saving myself a helluva lot of money and gaining at least 5 pounds in my quest. (See my Eating Cheap in Vegas list for the gems.) 

My experience at Fulton Fish Market was as close as I've been at eating "fresh" seafood. I know, I know. It's not even on the east coast, so I've never actually come close. I *will* make it out to Maine or Mass soon enough and see what I've been missing. In the meantime, this place really did it for me.

My clam chowder was fantastical. The perfect amount of salt, pepper and clams. I'm very particular about how I like the consistency and taste of my soup and it lived up to my expectations. I would absolutely, positively order it again. The only reason for not a perfect rating is I didn't particularly enjoy the bread bowl as much. I would have liked just a giant bowl of the soup with some crusty bread on the side.

My husband ordered the fish and chips. I know people out there hate the word 'amazing' but I can't think of anything else to describe it. The batter was perfect and crunched in your mouth, while the fish melted in your mouth. What an oddly perfect combination. The fries were good too--crispy and well seasoned--  and I think I gorged on them by dipping them in my soup.

I shouldn't have written this review at lunch time cause now I want some fish...

If you liked fried nummy seafood treats I sugest coming here. I also suggest sharing because the combo platter of chicken, shrimp, fish and fries has a ridiculous amount of food. The fish was just eh, shrimp was good (wish I had more in my platter), the chicken was really good and the fries were just meh. But for what I was looking for at the time it all hit the spot.

Although expect to wait a bit after you order. Service was a little slow, I think it's because they batter and fry it as you order rather than having it sit under a heat lamp.
This place is pretty yummy especially for everything being so deep fried but I have to say their soup in the bread bowl was just the best they have very big portions but worth it

Very bad attitude!  They ignored the customers while they talked about personal stuff. Two people in front of me decided not to order in frustration.  The fish is good if you can get past the bad attitude.
We always have to eat here when we come to Las Vegas.  Always good, never been disappointed!!! Fish and shrimp this time, very yummy and fries are the best!!! Highly recommend

We stopped by here for a quick snack while waiting for our show to start (Zumanity). That show was amazing by the way. There were surprisingly a lot of people wanting fish & chips at the same time as us so it was a good 15-minute from ordering to sitting down and eating--it was alright since we had time to kill. The food was tasty and not too oily. We were satisfied and good to go before the show with a subsequent a real dinner afterwards (Gordon Ramsay Steak). So if you need a quick snack while waiting for a show or something to start, you can't go wrong with Fulton Fish Market.

ordered Fish, Chicken, & Shrimp: came with 2 large fish pcs., 2 fried shrimp, and 2 dinky chicken strips. fish was nice, could use a touch of salt. Shrimp was crispy on the outside and tender inside. Chicken was tiny, but okay. Hush puppies standard as were the fries.
Probably won't be going back again. I have been coming here for years. The value just isn't there anymore. Smaller portions and not quality sides.
The fish is batter fried Cod which is really good.  It doesn't have a fishy taste at all.  Fries are awesome.
Yes, I can not stay away from this place when I go through Vegas for lunch.  It was as good as ever and the Ben and Jerry's next door is good for afterwards.

Pricey, but deliciously fried goodness! The fish and chips are AMAZING. Clam chowder sourdough bowl was average. The only downfall the fish had tons of residue oil on it. Fried clams were not worth the money, it was more fried bread than anything. Didn't taste any clam

Three people - we ordered the family meal. 
BIG MISTAKE.
There was enough food for double the amount of people.
So... think twice about that one.
But, the fish was great. So was the chicken. The shrimp were alright because they were a bit too battered. Service was fast and friendly. Definitely a good place to get a quick bite to eat while you ponder why the slots aren't paying and how many more drinks will it take to make you forget that you're bummed you're losing money in Vegas....

My favorite fish place to eat at while in Las Vegas Yes, it's always packed and a extremely long wait. However, it's worth the wait. The food is delicious and the staff is very nice! Best fish ... And shrimp in the country!
